500
00:35:54,944 --> 00:35:56,737
Is that a siren I'm hearing?

501
00:35:57,864 --> 00:36:00,449
I think you said
you'll persuade him quietly.

502
00:36:01,659 --> 00:36:04,537
The bad news must be
that you lost the medical officer.

503
00:36:04,620 --> 00:36:06,122
What's the worse news?

504
00:36:06,914 --> 00:36:09,792
There's someone else
who's looking for that medical officer.

505
00:36:12,461 --> 00:36:15,965
So there's someone else who's trying
to dig up the truth of the mine case?

506
00:36:17,842 --> 00:36:21,012
We don't know if they're trying
to dig it up or cover it up.

507
00:36:21,762 --> 00:36:22,889
One thing's for sure.

508
00:36:32,481 --> 00:36:34,984
A very annoying fly
is buzzing around us now.

509
00:36:42,283 --> 00:36:43,284
It's huge.

510
00:36:52,877 --> 00:36:53,920
What the heck?

511
00:36:54,003 --> 00:36:55,630
Why is Noh Tae-nam's dog here?

512
00:36:55,713 --> 00:36:59,592
Woo-in brought him after she arrested him
at the airport last time.

513
00:37:00,259 --> 00:37:01,302
I'm fostering him now.

514
00:37:01,385 --> 00:37:02,929
Woo-in cannot leave the base now.

515
00:37:03,804 --> 00:37:04,889
It's troublesome.

516
00:37:07,934 --> 00:37:10,603
You're going through a lot too.

517
00:37:12,438 --> 00:37:13,981
This is Medical Officer Jo's.

518
00:37:14,065 --> 00:37:16,025
Check it and see
if you can find anything useful.

519
00:37:18,194 --> 00:37:19,570
You brought this entire thing?

520
00:37:20,363 --> 00:37:22,323
Without permission? Jeez.

521
00:37:22,823 --> 00:37:24,033
How are you going
to deal with the aftermath?

522
00:37:24,700 --> 00:37:26,869
I just brought the search
and seizure forward.

523
00:37:27,662 --> 00:37:29,956
Because I'm going to get an arrest warrant
for Won Ki-choon soon.

524
00:37:30,831 --> 00:37:32,792
And this is a video of Won Ki-choon
when he was hospitalized.

525
00:37:32,875 --> 00:37:35,211
Run a program through it
and check its authenticity.

526
00:37:38,547 --> 00:37:41,008
I thought you'd just stay quiet
after you got punished.

527
00:37:41,092 --> 00:37:43,261
Just check those and call me.

528
00:37:43,886 --> 00:37:45,179
Wait.

529
00:37:46,681 --> 00:37:48,140
Take care of him for a while.

530
00:37:48,224 --> 00:37:51,185
I'm really allergic to dogs,
so I can't take care of him anymore.

531
00:37:51,269 --> 00:37:54,605
What? Hey, I can't keep him with me!

532
00:37:58,401 --> 00:38:00,111
He likes you.

533
00:38:00,194 --> 00:38:02,863
A serviceperson who got kicked out
of the base and a dog who lost his owner.

534
00:38:02,947 --> 00:38:05,157
You're both very pitiful.
Very similar. Right.

535
00:38:06,200 --> 00:38:07,118
You two look alike.

536
00:38:07,201 --> 00:38:09,453
You two look great together.
Even more than me.

537
00:38:09,537 --> 00:38:11,080
You can do it, Doh Bae-man.

538
00:38:11,831 --> 00:38:13,291
-Hey!
-Cheer up!

539
00:38:13,374 --> 00:38:14,500
Hey, wait.

540
00:38:14,583 --> 00:38:16,711
Kang Ha-joon!

541
00:38:17,420 --> 00:38:18,754
We don't look alike…

542
00:38:20,923 --> 00:38:22,717
What am I supposed to do with him?

543
00:38:22,800 --> 00:38:23,718
Stay.

544
00:38:24,302 --> 00:38:25,303
Stay.

545
00:38:25,886 --> 00:38:28,222
The military prosecutors
who stirred up controversy

546
00:38:28,306 --> 00:38:30,516
by causing an incident
at the military court regarding

547
00:38:30,599 --> 00:38:33,311
Battalion Commander Won
was sent to a disciplinary committee

548
00:38:33,394 --> 00:38:35,354
and received serious punishment.

549
00:38:35,438 --> 00:38:37,398
Ministry of National Defense
mentioned abuse of authority…

550
00:38:39,317 --> 00:38:40,443
What's this dog?

551
00:38:40,526 --> 00:38:41,527
Auntie.

552
00:38:43,070 --> 00:38:44,071
You're home.

553
00:38:45,573 --> 00:38:48,242
Hey, you're even bringing
a dog into the house?

554
00:38:49,410 --> 00:38:51,829
All right. I heard he's thirsty.

555
00:38:51,912 --> 00:38:54,915
-Hold him.
-Hey!

556
00:38:54,999 --> 00:38:56,334
Hey! Seriously…

557
00:38:57,501 --> 00:38:58,419
Wait.

558
00:38:59,128 --> 00:39:00,171
He looks familiar.

559
00:39:00,254 --> 00:39:01,255
This Doberman.

560
00:39:02,256 --> 00:39:03,674
Where did I see him?

561
00:39:03,758 --> 00:39:05,051
Come here.

562
00:39:05,134 --> 00:39:08,637
Come here, drink some water.
Come and drink water.

563
00:39:13,225 --> 00:39:14,810
You never showed yourself when I was busy.

564
00:39:15,644 --> 00:39:18,856
Hey, this place isn't just for you
to come when you're being punished!

565
00:39:20,066 --> 00:39:21,025
I…

566
00:39:21,984 --> 00:39:24,195
I had to wander around all day long today

567
00:39:24,278 --> 00:39:26,697
to investigate the case
of the hero of mines…

568
00:39:28,407 --> 00:39:30,576
I'm asking you as a detective,
so answer honestly.

569
00:39:30,659 --> 00:39:33,162
If you lie, I'm going to cuff you.

570
00:39:34,121 --> 00:39:35,414
I'm not kidding right now.

571
00:39:35,498 --> 00:39:37,458
It hurts! Auntie! What's wrong?

572
00:39:37,541 --> 00:39:39,418
You were at Club Cartel, weren't you?

573
00:39:40,211 --> 00:39:41,712
I saw that dog there.

574
00:39:41,796 --> 00:39:43,672
He's Noh Tae-nam's dog, isn't he?

575
00:39:45,007 --> 00:39:47,593
That rat who ran away while
he was drinking with Noh Tae-nam…

576
00:39:48,844 --> 00:39:49,887
Is it you, Bae-man?

577
00:39:51,972 --> 00:39:53,057
Auntie.

578
00:39:54,975 --> 00:39:56,685
That was in the past.

579
00:39:57,520 --> 00:39:58,729
In the past?

580
00:40:04,360 --> 00:40:05,444
So it was you.

581
00:40:05,945 --> 00:40:07,613
About that case…

582
00:40:09,490 --> 00:40:11,784
I was going to confess to you.

583
00:40:12,576 --> 00:40:13,744
Before that,

584
00:40:13,828 --> 00:40:15,663
there's a bigger story.

585
00:40:15,746 --> 00:40:17,832
What? There's a bigger story? What is it?

586
00:40:20,584 --> 00:40:21,836
It's about Mom and Dad.

587
00:40:26,465 --> 00:40:28,968
-Hey, what did you say?
-I don't know where to start…

588
00:40:29,802 --> 00:40:30,719
Auntie.

589
00:40:31,720 --> 00:40:33,806
-Listen to me.
-Hey, get out.

590
00:40:34,723 --> 00:40:36,308
Get out of this house, now!

591
00:40:36,934 --> 00:40:38,853
You're even using them as excuses?

592
00:40:38,936 --> 00:40:41,439
-That's not why. Listen to me.
-Get out!

593
00:40:41,522 --> 00:40:44,483
-Get out! I can't stand the sight of you!
-You're not even going to listen?

594
00:40:44,567 --> 00:40:46,110
Hey, take this dog with you!

595
00:40:46,193 --> 00:40:47,194
Get out!

596
00:40:48,154 --> 00:40:49,655
Stop yelling.

597
00:40:50,156 --> 00:40:52,408
-You're scaring the dog.
-Get out!

598
00:40:52,491 --> 00:40:53,492
Get out!

599
00:40:54,118 --> 00:40:56,620
I'm leaving.
Jeez. I was so doggone scared.

600
00:40:56,704 --> 00:40:58,038
Let's go.

601
00:40:58,622 --> 00:41:00,332
-Let's go.
-Don't ever come again!

602
00:41:01,417 --> 00:41:02,501
Bye.

603
00:41:09,383 --> 00:41:10,759
MINE EXPLOSION AT THE DMZ

604
00:41:12,219 --> 00:41:14,930
It said that Battalion Commander Won
didn't save my brother…

605
00:41:15,848 --> 00:41:17,808
but that he actually shot my brother.

606
00:41:26,233 --> 00:41:29,278
I sent you the information
on the members of the platoon

607
00:41:29,361 --> 00:41:31,071
who participated
in search and patrol that day.

608
00:41:35,701 --> 00:41:36,577
OFFICER PERSONNEL RECORD

609
00:41:36,660 --> 00:41:37,995
SOLDIER PERSONNEL RECORD

610
00:41:38,078 --> 00:41:39,288
SOLDIER PERSONNEL RECORD

611
00:41:45,711 --> 00:41:46,962
Yes, Prosecutor Doh.

612
00:41:47,046 --> 00:41:49,381
Mr. Kang is looking
for the medical officer.

613
00:41:49,465 --> 00:41:50,883
The clue will be out soon.

614
00:41:50,966 --> 00:41:54,428
I'm now checking the suspects who might
have sent the letter to Kim Han-yong.

615
00:41:56,931 --> 00:41:59,600
Noh Tae-nam's verdict
for his desertion is out.

616
00:42:00,351 --> 00:42:01,644
Kim Han-yong's verdict too.

617
00:42:01,727 --> 00:42:03,020
I know.

618
00:42:03,604 --> 00:42:05,856
Noh Tae-nam is going
to begin his military life

619
00:42:05,940 --> 00:42:07,566
after receiving a small punishment.

620
00:42:08,734 --> 00:42:11,695
Because not everything goes
according to plans.

621
00:42:11,779 --> 00:42:12,613
No.

622
00:42:13,155 --> 00:42:15,032
Everything's going according to my plan.

623
00:42:15,866 --> 00:42:18,160
-What?
-You'll see. Just wait.

624
00:42:19,954 --> 00:42:22,498
I sent a natural enemy to Noh Tae-nam,

625
00:42:23,290 --> 00:42:25,084
so his military life will be fun.

626
00:42:30,589 --> 00:42:32,174
I'm Sergeant Ahn Soo-ho.

627
00:42:32,883 --> 00:42:34,385
You're that famous Noh Tae-nam, right?

628
00:42:37,263 --> 00:42:40,224
We went to the same military prison,
and we're in the same base.

629
00:42:40,307 --> 00:42:41,934
This is a connection too.

630
00:42:42,017 --> 00:42:42,935
Let's get along.

631
00:42:47,189 --> 00:42:49,316
Looks like you don't want to get along?

632
00:42:50,109 --> 00:42:53,862
You must show people
that you are serving more diligently

633
00:42:53,946 --> 00:42:56,073
and sincerely than anyone else.

634
00:42:56,156 --> 00:42:58,951
This is the last chance I'm giving you.

635
00:43:01,203 --> 00:43:02,204
Nice to meet you.

636
00:43:03,122 --> 00:43:03,956
AHN SOO-HO

637
00:43:04,039 --> 00:43:05,124
Sergeant Ahn Soo-ho.

638
00:43:05,708 --> 00:43:07,167
Yes, Tae-nam.

639
00:43:07,251 --> 00:43:08,877
Just relax, okay?

640
00:43:51,253 --> 00:43:55,382
Okay, the platoon members will be back
after guard duty, so wait.

641
00:43:55,466 --> 00:43:56,967
Yes, sir.

642
00:43:58,469 --> 00:43:59,470
Hey.

643
00:44:00,054 --> 00:44:01,013
Why aren't you answering me?

644
00:44:01,847 --> 00:44:04,183
You're a new soldier,
and you're damn dazed!

645
00:44:04,892 --> 00:44:05,768
Yes, sir.

646
00:44:06,352 --> 00:44:07,519
Do it right.

647
00:44:20,908 --> 00:44:22,701
Is this a front-line base?

648
00:44:23,285 --> 00:44:24,745
To be exact, it's a GOP.

649
00:44:24,828 --> 00:44:26,872
This platoon guards the cease fire-line
24 hours a day.

650
00:44:27,623 --> 00:44:29,708
It's different from regular bases.

651
00:44:29,792 --> 00:44:31,293
How is it different?

652
00:44:31,877 --> 00:44:33,796
Below FEBA, there's no PX,

653
00:44:33,879 --> 00:44:36,298
and there's no leave,
spending nights out, or weekends either.

654
00:44:36,882 --> 00:44:38,759
Then what does this place have?

655
00:44:38,842 --> 00:44:40,678
Live ammunition and grenades.

656
00:44:42,304 --> 00:44:43,597
Grenades?

657
00:44:44,264 --> 00:44:45,265
What is it?

658
00:44:45,891 --> 00:44:47,184
Are you scared?

659
00:44:50,771 --> 00:44:52,439
You need to calm your temper here.

660
00:44:53,065 --> 00:44:55,192
Everyone here has live ammunition on them,

661
00:44:55,275 --> 00:44:57,945
so when something goes wrong, they just
fire their guns and throw the grenades.

662
00:45:02,032 --> 00:45:03,033
By the way,

663
00:45:03,742 --> 00:45:06,703
why did you go to military prison,
Sergeant Ahn?

664
00:45:07,329 --> 00:45:08,330
Me?

665
00:45:12,459 --> 00:45:13,544
Are you curious?

666
00:45:17,673 --> 00:45:19,174
I'll tell you in time.

667
00:45:23,345 --> 00:45:26,014
-We have new soldiers!
-They're here.

668
00:45:26,098 --> 00:45:27,433
Wow, isn't he a famous guy?

669
00:45:27,516 --> 00:45:29,476
-He looks so…
-Look at his eyes.

670
00:45:29,560 --> 00:45:30,811
They're vicious.

671
00:45:30,894 --> 00:45:32,187
Are you Noh Tae-nam?

672
00:45:37,609 --> 00:45:39,445
Wow, this is awesome!

673
00:45:43,365 --> 00:45:46,368
You must have done everything
to get money to play games here.

674
00:45:46,869 --> 00:45:49,538
Like, switching the CT scan images.

675
00:45:50,247 --> 00:45:51,748
Damn it.

676
00:45:52,666 --> 00:45:54,751
Military Doh!

677
00:45:56,628 --> 00:45:58,755
You must be struggling
after you got punished.

678
00:45:58,839 --> 00:46:00,966
You're here to rip off
someone winning money.

679
00:46:01,049 --> 00:46:02,968
What is it? Why are you doing this to me?

680
00:46:03,635 --> 00:46:05,554
-Are you guys on the same team?
-No.

681
00:46:07,055 --> 00:46:08,474
Why would you be interested in him?

682
00:46:09,558 --> 00:46:12,394
"Hachungbulga Yieoeobing."

683
00:46:12,478 --> 00:46:13,854
Do you even know what that means?

684
00:46:13,937 --> 00:46:18,150
"A bug that only lives during summer
cannot speak or explain about winter?"

685
00:46:18,233 --> 00:46:21,361
-Correct?
-Wow, you're intelligent, Military Doh.

686
00:46:23,739 --> 00:46:26,658
So it means someone ordered you
to catch the medical officer,

687
00:46:27,409 --> 00:46:30,037
and you're just a bug
who does what you're told to do,

688
00:46:30,120 --> 00:46:31,997
without thinking. Isn't that right?

689
00:46:33,624 --> 00:46:35,209
-A bug?
-Yes.

690
00:46:38,837 --> 00:46:40,172
Hey, Doh Bae-man.

691
00:46:40,255 --> 00:46:42,716
The lives of other people are all history.

692
00:46:43,675 --> 00:46:46,637
I live my life using my own brain too!

693
00:46:47,513 --> 00:46:48,514
Come with me.

694
00:46:48,597 --> 00:46:49,598
Kill him!

695
00:47:00,150 --> 00:47:01,401
Comrade Military Doh.

696
00:47:03,779 --> 00:47:07,241
Today, I can finally finish
what I couldn't finish last time.

697
00:47:11,787 --> 00:47:13,705
I'm sick of this.

698
00:47:14,373 --> 00:47:16,500
You bastard!

699
00:47:30,430 --> 00:47:31,557
You're actually cute.

700
00:47:35,102 --> 00:47:36,186
Excuse me.

701
00:47:36,270 --> 00:47:38,855
Was this the guy who was looking
for Medical Officer Jo?

702
00:47:40,524 --> 00:47:41,733
You came last time…

703
00:47:41,817 --> 00:47:43,026
By the way, are you okay?

704
00:47:43,110 --> 00:47:45,612
-Was he the one?
-No.

705
00:47:46,196 --> 00:47:48,031
-You have to get treated now…
-No.

706
00:47:48,115 --> 00:47:50,492
Are you sure you didn't get it mixed up?
I'm sure it's him.

707
00:47:50,576 --> 00:47:53,120
I can't get that man mixed up
with a gangster?

708
00:47:53,203 --> 00:47:55,539
He was a very gentle
and sophisticated gentleman.

709
00:47:56,748 --> 00:47:57,833
Then…

710
00:47:59,793 --> 00:48:00,836
was it him?

711
00:48:01,628 --> 00:48:03,964
Yes. It was him.

712
00:48:04,923 --> 00:48:07,134
-Are you sure?
-Of course.

713
00:48:07,759 --> 00:48:09,011
Okay, thank you.

714
00:48:13,765 --> 00:48:16,560
Yong Moon-goo was the one
who took and hid Medical Officer Jo?

715
00:48:16,643 --> 00:48:18,353
-Then did Noh Hwa-young--
-No.

716
00:48:19,187 --> 00:48:22,399
Yong Moon-goo knew nothing
about the Won Ki-choon case.

717
00:48:22,482 --> 00:48:25,402
About you breaking
Lieutenant Colonel Won's prosthetic leg…

718
00:48:25,485 --> 00:48:28,905
The Doh Bae-man I know wouldn't do that
without concrete physical evidence.

719
00:48:29,656 --> 00:48:30,907
What was the reason?

720
00:48:30,991 --> 00:48:32,868
If Noh Hwa-young ordered him to do that,

721
00:48:32,951 --> 00:48:35,495
he wouldn't have needed
to do it himself, like I have.

722
00:48:35,579 --> 00:48:39,207
Yong Moon-goo is doing things on his own
without Noh Hwa-young's orders?

723
00:48:39,291 --> 00:48:43,420
It means he is also curious
about the truth of the hero of mines case.

724
00:48:44,338 --> 00:48:47,299
By the way, what should we do,
since we lost the medical officer?

725
00:48:48,467 --> 00:48:50,302
I will give you a more certain card.

726
00:48:50,385 --> 00:48:52,679
Did you find the suspect
for the informant letter?

727
00:48:53,263 --> 00:48:54,681
I'll send you his address.

728
00:48:55,515 --> 00:48:56,516
Yes, sir.

729
00:49:29,216 --> 00:49:32,427
We totally preheated him
before you came here,

730
00:49:32,511 --> 00:49:34,638
so he'll tell you everything
you want to know.

731
00:49:35,222 --> 00:49:36,056
You're not bad.

732
00:49:37,474 --> 00:49:39,309
From now on, work like you're my shadow.

733
00:49:40,435 --> 00:49:42,521
Like you're not there,
though you're there.

734
00:49:42,604 --> 00:49:43,939
Like I'm not there.

735
00:49:44,439 --> 00:49:46,650
Wow, I love that.

736
00:49:46,733 --> 00:49:50,153
That also sounds like you're going
to take care of everything.

737
00:49:53,657 --> 00:49:56,535
I'm sure you switched
the Company Commander's CT scan images

738
00:49:56,618 --> 00:49:59,204
because there's something
that must not be revealed to the world.

739
00:49:59,287 --> 00:50:01,748
Because the thing that's stuck
in the Company Commander's head

740
00:50:01,832 --> 00:50:03,625
is a bullet, not mine fragments.

741
00:50:04,209 --> 00:50:05,377
Yes.

742
00:50:06,128 --> 00:50:07,421
That's true.

743
00:50:07,504 --> 00:50:09,256
Did Won Ki-choon order you to do it?

744
00:50:10,424 --> 00:50:11,925
Yes.

745
00:50:13,135 --> 00:50:14,594
Wasn't it someone above him?

746
00:50:15,345 --> 00:50:16,430
No.

747
00:50:16,513 --> 00:50:19,099
I got the order
from the Search Battalion Commander.

748
00:50:19,182 --> 00:50:21,435
Are you sure there isn't anyone else
besides Won Ki-choon?

749
00:50:22,018 --> 00:50:22,978
Yes.

750
00:50:26,022 --> 00:50:29,359
Now then, let's get to the actual point.

751
00:50:30,652 --> 00:50:33,739
-What?
-Tell me about Won Ki-choon's leg.

752
00:50:53,216 --> 00:50:59,055
TODAY'S LATE-NIGHT SNACK

753
00:50:59,890 --> 00:51:01,141
It's cold.

754
00:51:04,811 --> 00:51:06,062
I'm hungry.

755
00:51:08,273 --> 00:51:09,649
You're Sergeant Koo Hyun-seok

756
00:51:09,733 --> 00:51:11,651
of the Search Battalion
of the fourth division, right?

757
00:51:11,735 --> 00:51:14,154
It's cold. Did you get a lot of calls?

758
00:51:14,780 --> 00:51:16,031
Who are you?

759
00:51:16,114 --> 00:51:19,534
You left the letter in the Search
Company Commander's hospital room, right?

760
00:51:22,287 --> 00:51:24,623
-Who are you?
-Me?

761
00:51:26,625 --> 00:51:29,711
I'm the military prosecutor
who was in charge of Kim Han-yong's case.

762
00:51:30,378 --> 00:51:32,005
Did you leave the letter there?

763
00:51:33,256 --> 00:51:34,299
I didn't.

764
00:51:34,382 --> 00:51:36,176
I see…

765
00:51:37,761 --> 00:51:41,139
Don't most people ask what letter
it was first at times like this?

766
00:51:41,223 --> 00:51:42,641
If you really didn't, I mean.

767
00:51:42,724 --> 00:51:45,769
What you said means you know
what letter it is. Don't you think so?

768
00:51:46,603 --> 00:51:49,147
Don't accuse me. I have nothing to do
with that letter or whatever.

769
00:51:49,731 --> 00:51:53,235
The day you left the letter
happened to be the day of your discharge.

770
00:51:54,694 --> 00:51:57,155
That's an incredible coincidence,
don't you think?

771
00:51:57,239 --> 00:51:58,448
The handwriting is identical too.

772
00:52:00,450 --> 00:52:01,284
What is it?

773
00:52:01,910 --> 00:52:04,120
You couldn't muster up courage
while you were wearing a military uniform?

774
00:52:04,204 --> 00:52:05,997
Or should I say…

775
00:52:06,081 --> 00:52:09,042
Were you trying to reduce
some of that measly guilt?

776
00:52:09,876 --> 00:52:13,171
So did your guilt get reduced?

777
00:52:14,422 --> 00:52:15,590
Shut up!

778
00:52:15,674 --> 00:52:16,842
I got discharged!

779
00:52:17,759 --> 00:52:20,053
You have no right to do this to me.

780
00:52:20,554 --> 00:52:23,723
I will never get involved
with that disgusting military anymore!

781
00:52:23,807 --> 00:52:26,601
The letter you wrote
triggered Kim Han-yong.

782
00:52:30,730 --> 00:52:33,984
Kim Han-yong read your letter,
shot Won Ki-choon,

783
00:52:34,860 --> 00:52:36,152
and got sentenced to five years in prison.

784
00:52:37,612 --> 00:52:38,738
Five years?

785
00:52:38,822 --> 00:52:40,866
Hey, you shouldn't have left
the letter there at least.

786
00:52:40,949 --> 00:52:43,952
How are you going to reduce
your guilt for Kim Han-yong now?

787
00:52:45,620 --> 00:52:48,456
But you said the verdict is out.
Isn't it all over, then?

788
00:52:48,540 --> 00:52:49,374
No.

789
00:52:52,460 --> 00:52:53,920
Everything will start again.

790
00:52:54,629 --> 00:52:56,548
I heard you were the most loyal
to the Company Commander.

791
00:52:57,299 --> 00:53:01,136
Even though the military is disgusting,
you couldn't turn a blind eye.

792
00:53:05,599 --> 00:53:07,434
You're the only one
who can help the Company Commander now.

793
00:53:08,602 --> 00:53:10,145
Tell me the truth you know.

794
00:53:16,026 --> 00:53:18,194
That day was really foggy,

795
00:53:18,278 --> 00:53:20,655
so it was very difficult to
secure the front.

796
00:53:21,281 --> 00:53:22,365
Halt!

797
00:53:22,449 --> 00:53:23,533
A five-minute break!

798
00:53:23,617 --> 00:53:25,994
-A five-minute break!
-A five-minute break!

799
00:53:26,661 --> 00:53:30,165
During our patrol,
Battalion Commander Won Ki-choon

800
00:53:30,832 --> 00:53:33,460
was away for an urgent matter,

801
00:53:34,669 --> 00:53:36,296
and a water deer appeared.

802
00:53:38,924 --> 00:53:39,883
What?

803
00:53:40,550 --> 00:53:42,052
Isn't that a water deer?

804
00:53:43,053 --> 00:53:44,387
It looks like a water deer.

805
00:53:44,471 --> 00:53:45,513
What?

806
00:53:47,223 --> 00:53:48,516
Isn't that the direction
Battalion Commander Won went?

807
00:53:49,100 --> 00:53:50,352
Yes, I think it is.

808
00:53:50,435 --> 00:53:51,519
That's a minefield.

809
00:53:52,312 --> 00:53:54,522
If the water deer steps on a mine,
it will be a disaster.

810
00:53:55,357 --> 00:53:58,777
Hey, you guys wait here.
And be on watch properly.

811
00:53:59,611 --> 00:54:00,654
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

812
00:54:02,030 --> 00:54:04,240
I'm coming with you, Company Commander.

813
00:54:06,826 --> 00:54:07,827
Stay here.

814
00:54:20,423 --> 00:54:21,800
Who's there?

815
00:54:23,218 --> 00:54:24,636
Is that you, Company Commander?

816
00:54:33,853 --> 00:54:34,938
I said, who's there?

817
00:54:35,522 --> 00:54:37,023
Say your official rank and name,
or I'll fire!

818
00:54:51,538 --> 00:54:54,165
Battalion Commander!

819
00:54:54,833 --> 00:54:56,084
I said, who's there?

820
00:55:23,695 --> 00:55:26,156
Company Commander!

821
00:55:42,172 --> 00:55:43,882
If you begin re-investigating,

822
00:55:44,466 --> 00:55:47,469
then I will testify everything
in the court.

823
00:55:51,264 --> 00:55:52,640
I'll see you at the court.

824
00:55:55,310 --> 00:55:56,811
According to Sergeant Koo's testimony,

825
00:55:56,895 --> 00:56:00,065
Won Ki-choon shot
the Company Commander by accident,

826
00:56:00,148 --> 00:56:04,527
and in order to cover it up,
he was turned into the hero of mines.

827
00:56:05,361 --> 00:56:07,697
So Division Commander Noh
got involved with this.

828
00:56:08,364 --> 00:56:10,325
Then she should have
just punished Won Ki-choon.

829
00:56:10,408 --> 00:56:11,785
Why did she go that far?

830
00:56:12,660 --> 00:56:15,038
When a gunfire accident occurs at the DMZ
and results in a casualty,

831
00:56:15,121 --> 00:56:16,915
it wouldn't just end with Won Ki-choon.

832
00:56:17,624 --> 00:56:19,959
This case occurred as soon
as she became the Division Commander,

833
00:56:20,043 --> 00:56:21,586
which she has always dreamed of.

834
00:56:22,295 --> 00:56:24,464
Plus, Noh Tae-nam ran away,
and made it a parade of incidents.

835
00:56:24,547 --> 00:56:28,301
So she fabricated the case and turned
Won Ki-choon into the hero of mines?

836
00:56:29,886 --> 00:56:31,012
Wait.

837
00:56:31,596 --> 00:56:32,931
Then what about this matter?

838
00:56:40,271 --> 00:56:43,775
I checked its authenticity, but there's
no trace of correction or alteration.

839
00:56:43,858 --> 00:56:46,319
Even if the NFS analyzes it,
the result will be the same.

840
00:56:46,402 --> 00:56:47,904
Sergeant Koo's testimony matches it too.

841
00:56:48,530 --> 00:56:51,825
He said that Won Ki-choon
didn't hurt his leg that day.

842
00:56:52,617 --> 00:56:53,952
Then why did he lose his leg?

843
00:56:54,744 --> 00:56:55,745
It looks like…

844
00:56:57,372 --> 00:56:59,541
his leg was amputated before the trial.

845
00:57:01,501 --> 00:57:03,753
That's the only answer to that.

846
00:57:03,837 --> 00:57:05,088
What?

847
00:57:05,588 --> 00:57:07,715
His leg was amputated?

848
00:57:08,299 --> 00:57:09,384
Maybe…

849
00:57:10,927 --> 00:57:14,931
we're dealing with a monster
that's even worse than our imagination.

850
00:57:43,877 --> 00:57:46,671
Mr. Noh got placed
in his base without trouble.

851
00:57:46,754 --> 00:57:48,798
You must stay alert at all times.

852
00:57:48,882 --> 00:57:50,258
Whether it's Tae-nam or IM,

853
00:57:50,800 --> 00:57:54,679
your job is to prevent accidents
before they occur.

854
00:58:01,394 --> 00:58:05,064
There's something I found out
about Lieutenant Colonel Won's mine case.

855
00:58:06,483 --> 00:58:08,193
I'm sure I told you not to be

856
00:58:08,276 --> 00:58:11,446
too interested
in my division and my subordinate.

857
00:58:12,322 --> 00:58:14,699
Didn't you take my warning seriously?

858
00:58:15,617 --> 00:58:20,288
It's to prevent an accident
before it occurs, just like you said.

859
00:58:20,371 --> 00:58:23,833
As the CEO of IM,
and as your legal representative.

860
00:58:27,378 --> 00:58:30,256
Okay. What did you find out?

861
00:58:33,218 --> 00:58:36,304
The true main character
of the story of the hero of mines was you,

862
00:58:36,387 --> 00:58:38,431
not Won Ki-choon.

863
00:58:40,433 --> 00:58:43,019
The shooting accident in the minefield.

864
00:58:43,102 --> 00:58:44,938
If that was revealed to the world,

865
00:58:45,021 --> 00:58:47,148
you would have gone through
the humiliation of resigning

866
00:58:47,232 --> 00:58:49,776
right after your inauguration
as the Division Commander.

867
00:58:51,486 --> 00:58:54,405
Plus, Mr. Noh's trial was going on too.

868
00:58:54,489 --> 00:58:57,033
So you're saying
I made Won Ki-choon a hero?

869
00:58:59,786 --> 00:59:01,829
You have a wild imagination, Lawyer Yong.

870
00:59:01,913 --> 00:59:04,332
I'm already convinced by that.

871
00:59:06,459 --> 00:59:09,379
There's something else
I'm really curious about.

872
00:59:10,880 --> 00:59:12,257
It's about Won Ki-choon's leg.

873
00:59:28,690 --> 00:59:30,358
Please save me, Division Commander!

874
00:59:31,109 --> 00:59:32,944
Just give me orders.

875
00:59:33,027 --> 00:59:35,613
I'll… I'll do everything.

876
00:59:36,114 --> 00:59:36,990
Yes.

877
00:59:38,449 --> 00:59:40,118
You must do everything.

878
00:59:42,036 --> 00:59:43,246
Adjutant Yang!

879
00:59:52,338 --> 00:59:53,464
Division Commander!

880
00:59:54,173 --> 00:59:55,133
What are you doing?

881
00:59:58,970 --> 01:00:00,471
Lieutenant Colonel Won Ki-choon.

882
01:00:00,555 --> 01:00:01,931
Yes, Division Commander.

883
01:00:02,015 --> 01:00:05,393
You can become a serviceperson
who shot your subordinate,

884
01:00:05,476 --> 01:00:09,188
or a hero who will be praised forever
by all servicepeople.

885
01:00:09,272 --> 01:00:11,899
I will do as you command,
Division Commander!

886
01:00:26,914 --> 01:00:28,541
Be a real hero,

887
01:00:29,626 --> 01:00:30,793
for me.

888
01:01:43,991 --> 01:01:45,535
You lost one leg,

889
01:01:46,077 --> 01:01:47,537
but you earned the world.

890
01:01:50,998 --> 01:01:53,501
You don't need to play a hero anymore.

891
01:01:53,584 --> 01:01:55,586
Because you've become a real hero now.

892
01:01:56,879 --> 01:01:58,548
If you get an honorable discharge,

893
01:01:58,631 --> 01:02:02,093
so many places will be desperate
to make you an assemblyman.

894
01:02:04,345 --> 01:02:06,764
Minister Lee Jae-sik and I

895
01:02:06,848 --> 01:02:09,308
will guide you through
that path you cannot walk.

896
01:02:24,741 --> 01:02:25,783
It's been cut off.

897
01:02:32,039 --> 01:02:33,583
I cut it off.

898
01:02:58,691 --> 01:03:01,319
This surgery is about taking out
what's stuck in his brain,

899
01:03:01,402 --> 01:03:02,779
so we have to think of
the worst-case scenario too.

900
01:03:02,862 --> 01:03:04,655
The search battalion member
who was at the scene

901
01:03:04,739 --> 01:03:06,199
will have a press conference
for his conscience.

902
01:03:06,282 --> 01:03:07,241
What?

903
01:03:07,325 --> 01:03:11,370
We must find evidence
and damage Noh Hwa-young.

904
01:03:11,454 --> 01:03:13,122
Today's press conference
has been canceled!

905
01:03:13,206 --> 01:03:14,499
-It's been canceled!
-No, it hasn't!

906
01:03:14,582 --> 01:03:16,834
Doh Bae-man, that lunatic!

907
01:03:16,918 --> 01:03:17,835
That's enough.

908
01:03:17,919 --> 01:03:21,506
Once you cross the line,
your fate will change.

909
01:03:21,589 --> 01:03:24,592
This case isn't just a simple
made-up story of the hero of mines.

910
01:03:24,675 --> 01:03:26,761
It's a trailer for a colossal gate.

911
01:03:30,139 --> 01:03:35,186
Subtitle translation by: Hae-lim Lee

